description: "Attorney of Love": Dozing off during an episode of Ally McLaw, Veronica dreams of being a stylish young lawyer herself! But she's not just any lawyer, her practice consists purely of affairs of the heart! Her first case: represent the 'girls' of Riverdale High, who claim the defendant, Betty Cooper, is monopolizing Archie's time! Before the case is over, Jughead and Cheryl get into the act, and you can bet that all's fair in love and court cases!

"Do You Want To Be A Millionaire... Again?!" by George Gladir & Jeff Schultz: Veronica accidentally activates a slot machine, and hits the jackpot! This doesn't go over too well with the less wealthy folks! Will Veronica be greedy and keep it all to herself, or will she find her charitable side? "Best Buds" by Gladir & Schultz: Veronica spends a weekend at a wealthy friend's mansion to get away from all the boring conversations of Riverdale's 'commoners.' Two days of dry name-dropping and she can't wait to talk to her friends back home again! "The Dream Tune" by Vic Lockman & Schultz: Veronica is determined to 'dream up' a hit tune, literally! When she wakes up, will it be music to anyone's ears?!

"Turnabout is Fair Play": In this riotous sequel to "Please Don't Repeat Yourself" from Veronica #109, it's déjà vu all over again yet again when the mystical pendent that gave her so much trouble returns! Back then, Veronica was doomed to reliving her day over... and over... and over again! Now it's even worse ?? the old body switcheroo that makes Veronica live in her mom's body and vice versa! Can Riverdale adjust to a Mrs. Lodge who acts young, fresh and trendy? Better yet, can they adjust to a Veronica with manners and culture?

name: Cip & Ciop e due scoiattoli e un bebè
O Detetive Que Veio Do Frio
O Grande Prêmio De Vila Xurupita

description:
They are called the “tzantzas”: these are heads made smaller and mummified by an Indio tribe, the Jivaros. This macabre “gadget” is tempting to many rich people; this is why the antique dealer William Murdock, from Bogotà, asks Mister No to bring him one of them. Daniel, Murdock’s younger brother, also leaves with Jerry, and Daniel’s rashness involves the pilot in a dangerous jaguar hunt…

"Tutto Mister No" n. 32 released on January, 1992.
name: I Cacciatori di Teste

description:
Badly hurt after saving Daniel Murdock’s life (Daniel had been attacked by a jaguar), Mister No is unable to stop the young man from making a wicked decision. The Jivaros by this time have stopped waging war against the enemy tribe, and so they no longer “produce” the tzantzas…To obtain the coveted heads, Murdock persuades them to attack their ex enemies, the Aguarunas. But the reaction of the Indios will be ferocious and no one will escape their rage!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 33 released on February, 1992.
name: Morte nella Foresta

description:
Night falls over the Pre-Colombian ruins of San Agustín, on the Cordillera of the Andes. And with darkness arrives the ferocious “Jaguar God”, who sows the seeds of death. But is the mysterious serial killer a man or a spirit? This is the question that arises in Mister No’s mind, on reaching San Agustín with Professor Bishop. There is no easy answer….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 34 released on March, 1992.
name: Il Dio Giaguaro

description:
The Jaguar God mystery begins to unravel. Maybe the land owner Carrillo is hiding behind the mask. But why would he want to kill? And what is the role of Erik Svenson, the owner of the Ranchos de Los Idolos, and his beautiful wife Blanche, who has her eyes on Mister No? The solution to the mystery will be unpredictable and tragic….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 35 released on April, 1992.
name: L'Artiglio Insanguinato

description:
The world’s green lung is suffering. United Highways is constructing a freeway that will cross the Amazon forest. Unprincipled technicians deviate the river, provoking a huge flood. The Indios rebel and attack the men from the company. It takes all Mister No’s skills to avoid a massacre!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 36 released on May, 1992.
name: La Lama di Asfalto

description:
Mister No is able to redirect the river, deviated by the United Highways, back onto its natural course, but the insolent officials have another idea. By poisoning the food given to the Indios, they cause carnage: nothing must be allowed to prevent the advance of “progress”. But maybe Mister No, helped by the honest engineer Nicholson, can stop them…

"Tutto Mister No" n. 37 released on June, 1992.
name: Terra Crudele

description:
Maybe the seducer Mister No has found his match! To win a aeroplane contest in Acapulco, Jerry fights hard against Deborah Winter, a sexy and spirited aviator. But an old acquaintance of Mister No’s, “Tango” Martínez, the underworld ringleader who drew him to Mexico by deception, wants our hero to help him in some fishy business. To persuade him, he has no qualms about kidnapping Deborah!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 38 released on July, 1992.
name: Bienvenido a Mexico!

description:
"Tango" Martínez wants Mister No to recover the six hundred million dollars that he and his gang stole from the Bank of Puebla. He needs it to get back into big-time organized crime and to get even with his rival, the gangster Felipe Ugarte. Jerry finds the loot among the archaeological ruins of Monte Albàn: but another player enters the mortal match….

"Tutto Mister No" n. 39 released on August, 1992.
name: Appuntamento in Nero

description:
With the help of Miguel Gallego, Lieutenant in the Puebla police force (who initially believes he is hand in glove with “Tango Martínez”), Mister No has a good chance of liberating his friend Deborah… But among his gaolers there’s El Buclecito, the top-class Mexican wrestler!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 40 released on September, 1992.
name: Il Re del Ring

description:
Jerry’s new client is Mister Stark, a businessman who wants to establish a canned meat factory in Selva Preta, in the heart of the Amazon forest. But this green hell will not tolerate intruders: monstrous mutant insects (that have become gigantic as a result of American experiments) attack Stark’s factory, massacring men and animals, and spreading terror. They are enormous and seem indestructible: for Mister No, Stark and the others the end seems near!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 41 released on October, 1992.
name: Il Mistero di Selva Preta

description:
A handful of men have barricaded themselves in Stark’s factory. Outside there are gigantic insects greedy for meat…their meat! All seems lost, when Phil Rover, a zoology student, manages to create a chemical compound able to kill these horrendous mutant creatures!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 42 released on November, 1992.
name: I Giorni del Terrore

description:
Gabriel, son of the rich Paraguayan Don Vicente Decano, has been kidnapped by mysterious armed men who are demanding a ransom of fifty thousand dollars. But Decano doesn’t want to pay and puts Mister No and his new client, the amiable Sanders, in charge of snatching his heir from the kidnappers. In order to find him, the two men have to enter the Paraguayan Chaco, in the land of the dreaded Ayoréos Indios, better known as the Moros!

"Tutto Mister No" n. 43 released on December, 1992.
name: Nella Terra dei Moros

description: Two of the most outrageous characters to grace the comics medium face off in future San Francisco. Marshal Law, fresh from his adventures with the Savage Dragon, is ready to give up his war against superheroes. But when his most hated enemy, the Sleepman who murdered his girlfriend, gets a hold of the Mask and unleashes murder and mayhem across the Bay, Law has to get back to his old tricks. It's not a question of which one of them will survive, so much as whether or not anyone else in Northern California will!

1. Roller Bunny! (Bugs Bunny)
 
2. Starspieler
 
3. Bretthart!! (Sylvester)
name: Roller Bunny!
